We believe in enhancing the child’s exposure to a wide range of topics and choices.  By doing so this will cause the child to grow and become well rounded in life.  Our ultimate goal is for every child to Grow feeling valued, feeling loved, feeling a sense of self- worth and importance, and to Grow knowing that they are special and Knowledge is Power.

All Saints is successful because of the commitment of all those associated with the school to provide a quality Catholic education.

name: ALL SPORTS CAMP
details: All Sports Camp was established to provide child day camp solutions for children 5-13 years old. Children must be able to be supervised in the stated counselor to camper ratios.  The staff recognizes the importance of balanced growth so they provide opportunities for mental, physical and emotional growth through a variety of creative experiences. Children are encouraged to learn and explore at their own speed in areas that interest them. We are pleased that you have chosen to include us in the growth and development of your children.

details: All the Children of the World Academy (ATC) is a Christian school dedicated to the social, emotional and academic growth of all students. We place importance on preparing a rich environment, which allows children to explore and make connections. Our preschool is play-based and incorporates the development of each child’s oral language, reading, writing, mathematics, science, health, social studies, and critical thinking skills. Our kindergarten uses age appropriate, integrated thematic instruction incorporating all areas of the school age curriculum. At ATC, children learn from specialists in the curricular areas of art, music, physical education, foreign language, and library.

name: ALTA HEAD START CAMP CHALLENGE
details: Alta Head Start/ Early Head Start offers quality educational programs in a nurturing, secure and developmental appropriate setting for children birth to five. Qualified, credentialed teachers who are trained in best practice academic and social- emotional standards, as well as other trained support staff, provide children a preschool experience focused on school readiness skill development. Children qualify for services based on federal income guidelines

details: Most students enrolled at the ALC are identified as having special needs entitling them to individualized accommodations designed to aid in their educational success. On the continuum of special education options defined by the Ohio Department of Education (ODE), students referred to the ALC have been identified as being best served in a separate educational facility. Our goal is to assist all students in acquiring the necessary emotional and behavioral skills to return to their home schools.

In our cooperative and inspirational environment, we aspire to empower the whole child as each successfully continues on a journey of life-long learning in an everchanging world.

name: AMELIA ELEMENTARY SCHOOL
details: Amelia has approximately 800 students enrolled in preschool through fifth grade and employs a staff of 37 full time teachers and health aide. Many families have chosen our school because of its moderate size, a growing parent support and involvement base, and the high quality education provided to our students by a highly qualified staff. Eighty-two (82%) of our teachers hold a Master’s Degree. Amelia is committed to a strong literacy and mathematics program. Specialized support in reading and math are provided in addition to regular classroom instruction. We realize that students learn in a variety of ways so we provide support in special education for qualifying students.

name: EAST LIVERPOOL CHRISTIAN SCHOOL
details: The vision for East Liverpool Christian School is “Providing educational opportunities founded on Christian principles, enabling students to impact society for Christ by continuously learning, discerning, and advocating truth.” ELCS provides a distinctively Christian education with academic excellence that equips each student to choose a life completely obedient to God.

name: ANGELINE SCHOOL
details: Our program providing services to children with developmental disabilities and their families is called the Angeline School.  It is our belief, based on sound research and evidence, that the earlier we are able to intervene with children and families experiencing a developmental disability the more positive the outcome.  We provide these services as efficiently and effectively as possible through such programs as Early Intervention, P.L.A.Y. Project (Play and Language for Autistic Youngsters), Responsive Teaching, and state licensed special education preschool and school-age services.

name: ANNA MARIE AYERS ELEMENTARY SCHOOL
details: We use the “Quality Change” process in our building. This is a goal oriented and data driven process that drives not only our instruction, but also our daily classroom and building routines. Our Mission Statement here at Ayers Elementary is: Ayers Elementary working together to be responsible, respectful, and successful. Our building goals are to improve: Reading, Writing, Math, and Behavior.

details: Our church family is warm, friendly, and welcoming. And best of all, you can come as you are: Jeans, shorts, or even dressed up if that’s what you like to do!

name: ANNUNCIATION
details: Through a dynamic and collaborative relationship (in which we expect and promote respect, prompt communication, understanding, and accountability), we can better foster the mission of Annunciation School. At its heart, that mission is to prepare your child to “confidently meet life’s future challenges” by “enhancing… [his/her] spiritual, intellectual, emotional, and physical wellbeing.”

name: ARCHBOLD ELEMENTARY SCHOOL
details: Archbold Elementary houses grades K-4 along with our county run pre-school units.  We have four to five sections of each grade level with approximately 100 students per grade.  When staff and students walk through the doors of Archbold Elementary School, they automatically become members of the AES Club where Attitude + Effort =Success and we are Respectful, Responsible, and Safe!  It is our goal at Archbold Elementary to ensure every student finds SUCCESS!

name: ARCHBOLD HIGH SCHOOL
details: Archbold High School is a 9-12th grade school with a tremendous staff and an excellent student body!  AHS offers numerous elective courses in drama, music,  computer and technology, industrial arts, art, business, and vocational education, as well as rigorous core curriculum offerings.  AHS supports 18 varsity sports as well as several very active student and booster groups. Archbold High School student success is due to continual support from our community!

name: ARCHBOLD MIDDLE SCHOOL
details: AMS is a special place for students to learn and grow.  We have a strong COMMUNITY of students and staff for the 2017-2018 school year!  It is inspiring to visit the classrooms and be involved in the challenging and motivating lessons that our students are engaged in every day.  No matter the specific role a TEAM member plays; from cook, to teacher, to custodian, all are committed to providing every student with an extremely positive school experience.
